do i have body dismorphic disorder this is what i feel i absoulutely hate when people stare at me it just makes me angry i say in my mind i get it already i am ugly i can look in the mirror for hours i look in photographs and try to deny forever that that is actually me in the pictures i just say horrible things to myself that i don't want to say them out loud i feel like i don't deserve to be loved or touched by a boy because i am hideous and don't deserve it i feel so violated and ashamed of myself when a guy talks and flirts with a girl the exact opposite of me physically i just turn like a different person and anger boils inside of me i will look down when i am walking in the halls avoiding all eyecontact everybody has a variety of emotions that run through them on a daily basis but what can you do but accept yourself for how you think you seem to have great insight into who you are you are very articulate and intelligent probably very pretty as well i know you will gain confidence in the future especially once you find the right guy he will bring new confidence to you as you realize you can talk to him about anything that is what i have found in my boyfriend when i was in high school i thought i was too ugly to leave the house believe it or not eventually a teacher came to the school once a week for my lessons to get the truant officers off my back but now i'm it seems like a million years ago another lifetime look at my icon do i look ugly to you i had a minor nose job six months ago but before that i was never ugly i realized Friends Social rule About a Boy Kodocha Boston Public Asperger syndrome Sin City A Course In Miracles Hulk (comics) Shaggy dog story Borderline personality disorder One Tree Hill (TV series) EastEnders Milton H. Erickson Mojave people Avenue Q Main characters of Fullmetal Alchemist Urusei Yatsura Jean Grey Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Ranma __ characters Phoebe Halliwell Characters in the Smurfs Sant Thakar Singh Humphrey Bog